description: The Ministry of Education in Ramallah has set up an online exam for high school students in the coastal enclave. According to the United Nations, 97% of Gaza's schools have been destroyed or damaged by Israeli air strikes.

The women of the Clain family: A story of ordinary jihadism
description: Jennyfer Clain, a niece of the Clain brothers – the propagandists for the Islamic State group (IS) who claimed responsibility for the November 13, 2015 terror attacks in Paris – as well as Christine Allain and Mayalen Duhart all face accusations of having joined IS in Syria between 2014 and 2017.

headline: 'In the United States, monopoly capitalism leads to underinvestment and to the concentration of wealth'
description: By analyzing the evolution of capitalism in the US since the 1960s, economist Patrick Artus argues that redistributive capitalism is the most effective, contrary to current practices.

headline: Armand Duplantis breaks another record and claims a third world title
description: The Swedish athlete won his third world championship title on Monday in Tokyo, finishing ahead of his Greek rival, Emmanouil Karalis. In a flawless final, he drew on Karalis's challenge for motivation and went on to break the world record for the 14th time, clearing 6.30 meters.

headline: 'French workers face not a Great Resignation, but a great disappointment'
description: Christine Erhel, an economist, and Bruno Palier, a research director at the French National Centre for Scientific Research, explain in an interview with Le Monde the growing rift between employees and employers, and propose solutions to improve the quality of working life.

description: In 50 years, the 8th arrondissement of the French capital, home to the Champs-Elysées and the 'Golden Triangle,' has lost nearly half its population. The mass acquisition of real estate by ultra-wealthy foreigners has driven locals out.

headline: Sanctions against Russia spark rift between US and Europe over China
description: Before increasing pressure on Vladimir Putin, Donald Trump is demanding his European allies stop importing Russian oil and gas and raise tariffs on Chinese goods. The EU, which will present a 19th sanctions package against Russia on Monday, finds these demands unacceptable.
byline: Harold Thibault,  Philippe Jacqué and  Philippe Ricard

headline: 'Not a job, but a love story': Morocco's racing pigeon craze
description: Unlike Europe, where the number of breeders is declining, Moroccans are embracing pigeon racing with enthusiasm. In Casablanca, more than 1,000 fanciers are concerned about rising temperatures that threaten their birds.
